An investor group headed byMinneapolis, Minn., broker Jeffrey Wendel said it raised itsstake in Zondervan Corp to 292,900 shares, or 7.1 pct of thetotal outstanding, from 238,900 shares, or 5.8 pct.    In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission,the Wendel group said it bought 54,000 Zondervan common sharesbetween March 24 and April 3 at prices ranging from 27.87 to29.96 dlrs a share.    The Wendel group has acted in cooperation with anothershareholder group headed by London investor Christopher Moran,who sought unsuccessfully last year to take over Zondervan. Reuter&#3;